SIMPLE: diamagnetism
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Diamagnetism
<hw>Di`a*mag"net*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The science which treats of diamagnetic phenomena, and of the
properties of diamagnetic bodies.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The magnetic action which characterizes diamagnetic
substances, the magnetic moments of which tend to oppose an externally
applied magnetic field. Contrasted with <contr>paramagnetism</contr> and
<contr>ferromagnetism</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Diamantiferous</ent>⟦br⟧
